[1]
Date: 14 Aug 2003
From: "sgrenard" <sgrenard@si.rr.com>

But for a more serious look, no pun intended, at crocodilian
pathophysiology, including contenders for this condition, readers may be
interested in the following 2002 review paper by Huchzermeyer
<http://www.oie.int/eng/publicat/rt/2102/HUCHZERMEYER.pdf>.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[Briefly, this article thoroughly covers a number of crocodilian diseases,
some rare, some common, but a good review of the diseases and how they
affect the animal. - Mod.TG]
******
